ir is a Canadian study based on very long term data which reached this conclusion.] The results of several decades of data demonstrate that homeschooling is an effective method of educating children. Period. &#10;If you think that it is possible to write a statute that will completely negate the effects of poor parental choices you are wrong. In Virginia and much of the United States the good news is that you can raise your own children pretty much however you see fit, the bad news is that so can your neighbors. A statute sufficient to address this example of very poor parental choices would also strip the parental rights of the many good parents [both homeschoolers and otherwise] and would needlessly burden most people. &#10;The state's right to direct the education of these children is, and always will be, secondary to the parent's rights to raise them according to their values and traditions. However misguided in this case the parents still have the right to decide these issues for their children. &#10;And, leave it to the Washington Post to find a true outlier in the world of homeschooling. No sense running a story about homeschool achievement, those stories are entirely too typical to warrant coverage! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1522" language="en" documentId="196" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="cathiemiller" date="7/29/2013 9:52 PM GMT+0200" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.washingtonpost.com/local/students-home-schooling-highlights-debate-over-va-religious-exemption-law/2013/07/28/ee2dbb1a-efbc-11e2-bed3-b9b6fe264871_comment.html?commentID=washingtonpost.com/ECHO/item/1375127556-827-581" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="196" notes="" title="Student’s home-schooling highlights debate over Va. religious exemption law"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="515"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="516" end="1034"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="1035" end="1315"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="1316" end="1522"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>